Package: RcppConcaveman
Type: Package
Title: A Very Fast 2D Concave Hull Algorithm in C++
Version: 1.0
Date: 2020-03-18
Authors@R: c(
  person("Jean-Romain", "Roussel", email="jean-romain.roussel.1@ulaval.ca", role = c("cre", "aut")), 
  person("Stanislaw", "Adaszewski", role = c("aut", "cph")))
Description: The concaveman function is a C++ implementation of the 'concaveman' (<https://github.com/mapbox/concaveman>) 
    algorithm from 'mapbox'. It is based on an original idea of Park and Oh (2012) (<http://www.iis.sinica.edu.tw/page/jise/2012/201205_10.pdf>).
    It computes a concave polygon for a set of points.
